# AOLRC UI Compatibility Rule

This older rule remains only as a compatibility pointer.

For current UI work, use these sources of truth first:

- `AGENTS.md`
- `UI_COMPONENTS.md`
- `RESPONSIVE_UI_RULES.md`
- `UI_REGRESSION_CHECKLIST.md`
- `.cursor/rules/UI-SHARED-PRIMITIVES-AOLRC.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/UI-INVENTORY-ROWS-AOLRC.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/UI-RESPONSIVE-QA-AOLRC.mdc`
- `.cursor/rules/UI-NON-HAPPY-PATH-STATES-AOLRC.mdc`

Still required:

- Build mobile-first and verify the shared breakpoints at `375`, `768`, `973`, `1199`, and `1440`.
- Keep operational workflows usable without horizontal scrolling on small screens.
- Reuse the shared toolbar, header, chip, form, and inventory-row primitives before adding page-local markup or CSS.
